# Postman API Testing Guide

This guide provides the exact URLs, HTTP methods, and data payloads to test your Event Management API endpoints in Postman.

## Base URL
**`http://localhost:5000/api/v3/app`**

---

## 1. Create an Event
**Endpoint:** `POST /events`
**URL:** `http://localhost:5000/api/v3/app/events`

**Body Type:** `form-data` (Required for file upload)

| Key | Value (Example) | Type |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| [name](file:///c:/Users/jeswa/Downloads/proje%20events/config/multer.js#17-24) | Tech Conference 2024 | Text |
| `tagline` | Innovating the Future | Text |
| `schedule` | 2024-12-25T10:00:00Z | Text |
| `description` | Annual tech gathering of innovators | Text |
| `moderator` | John Doe | Text |
| `category` | Technology | Text |
| `sub_category` | AI | Text |
| `rigor_rank` | 5 | Text |
| `files[image]` | [Select a file] | **File** |

---

## 2. Get Latest Events (Pagination)
**Endpoint:** `GET /events`
**URL:** `http://localhost:5000/api/v3/app/events?type=latest&limit=5&page=1`

**Query Params:**
- `type`: `latest` (Required)
- `limit`: `5` (Optional, default 5)
- `page`: `1` (Optional, default 1)

**Response:** Returns a list of events with pagination metadata.

---

## 3. Get Event by ID
**Endpoint:** `GET /events`
**URL:** `http://localhost:5000/api/v3/app/events?id=<YOUR_EVENT_ID>`

> **Note:** First create an event, then copy the `_id` from the response to test this endpoint.

**Query Params:**
- `id`: `<The Event ID>`

---

## 4. Update Event
**Endpoint:** `PUT /events/:id`
**URL:** `http://localhost:5000/api/v3/app/events/<YOUR_EVENT_ID>`

**Body Type:** `form-data`

| Key | Value (Example) | Type |
| :--- | :--- | :--- |
| [name](file:///c:/Users/jeswa/Downloads/proje%20events/config/multer.js#17-24) | Updated Tech Conference | Text |
| `tagline` | New Tagline | Text |
| `files[image]` | [Select new file] | **File** (Optional) |

---

## 5. Delete Event
**Endpoint:** `DELETE /events/:id`
**URL:** `http://localhost:5000/api/v3/app/events/<YOUR_EVENT_ID>`

**Response:** Returns success message if deleted.
